Interface DeletionBlockerListener<T extends DomainObject>


  • public interface DeletionBlockerListener<T extends DomainObject>
    A DeletionBlockerListener gives its implementations a chance to aid domain objects in determining whether they can be safely deleted.

    • Method Detail

      • getDeletionBlockers

        void getDeletionBlockers(T object,
                       Collection<String> blockers)
        Returns a list of all the blockers that prevent this object from being deleted. Each blocker must be returned as a human-friendly textual description of the blocker, ideally in the user's preferred language (if applicable).
        Parameters:
        object - The object being checked.
        blockers - A mutable collection where all the blockers that may prevent this object from being deleted should be added.
